Question: All possible ways to declare an array in JAVA
Source: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/1200621/declare-array-in-java

NOTE: Every array of any Primitive(int,char,......,etc) OR ObjectTypes(LinkedList[] <--- array of linked list)
      is an " instantiated object". i.e. Every array (be it of primitive or object type is an "object")

For Integer Array:
1.int[] intArray = new int[3];
2.int[] intArray = new int[]{10,20,30};
3.int[] intArray = {10,20,30};

For String Array:
String[] myStringArray = new String[3];
String[] myStringArray = new String[]{"a","b","c"};
String[] myStringArray = {"a","b","c"};
